makeboot - write a boot disk
Executable: /bin/makeboot.sh
Alias: makeboot

DESCRIPTION
  Writes the ReMinux net-
  installer to a floppy disk
  in an attached disk drive
  so the disk can boot a fresh
  ComputerCraft computer.

USAGE
  makeboot

REQUIREMENTS
  - A disk drive must be
    attached to the computer
    and detected at boot
    (_G.diskside is set by
    /boot/init.sys).
  - The disk must be empty;
    if /disk/startup already
    exists makeboot refuses
    to overwrite it.
  - HTTP must be enabled in
    the CC: Tweaked config so
    wget can fetch the
    installer.

NOTES
  The installer is fetched
  from the upstream repository
  on raw.githubusercontent.com
  and written to /disk/startup.
  The disk is then labelled
  'ReMinuxinstall'.

  Insert the disk into a fresh
  computer and reboot it; the
  net-installer will guide
  through installation source
  and type selection.

SEE ALSO
  apt     - package manager
  doctor  - audit/repair
